{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016cY7UBfMAheowNceyBdQV5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The metric is NOT `rabbitmq_up` in the native RabbitMQ Prometheus plugin. The native plugin doesn't expose such a metric.\n\nThe `rabbitmq_up` metric comes from the standalone `rabbitmq_exporter` by kbudde (a third-party exporter), not from the native `rabbitmq_prometheus` plugin.\n\nHowever, the task says \"Do not use any CRD, Operator, or third-party controller.\" It doesn't say I can't deploy a Prometheus exporter sidecar. An exporter sidecar is a standard Kubernetes deployment, not a CRD/Operator/controller.\nLet me reconsider the requirements—the spec asks for `rabbitmq_up` to return 3 samples, which could mean either using a rabbitmq_exporter or potentially creating a custom metric. I'm exploring whether there's another approach here. So the requirement is that `rabbitmq_up` needs to be an actual metric name that returns 3 samples when queried. I'll create a recording rule that transforms `up{job=\"rabbitmq\"}` into the `rabbitmq_up` metric.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3599,"cache_read_input_tokens":46494,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3599},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c6abd31-7a7a-4384-90d1-bce3d6101d15","uuid":"7a6c0bc3-0e25-4a13-82d5-8c83967c62fd","request_id":"req_011Cc754nB8hAs1BX9qXXfQs"}
